---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Prompt from '../components/Prompt.astro';
---
<Base title="About — John Soh" description="John Soh is a senior DevRel and AI engineer at Virtuals Protocol, working on the Agent Commerce Protocol.">
  <Prompt text="cat about.md" />
  <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:16px; margin:8px 0 20px;">
    <div style="width:52px; height:52px; border-radius:50%; background:var(--raise); border:1px solid var(--accent); display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;" class="mono" aria-hidden="true">
      <span style="color:var(--accent); font-size:15px;">JS</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h1 style="font-size:20px;">John Soh</h1>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:12px; color:var(--dim);">sr devrel + ai engineer @ virtuals</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="prose" style="color:var(--dim); max-width:60ch;">
    <p>
      I'm a Senior DevRel Engineer at Virtuals Protocol. I build the developer
      community around AI agents and the Agent Commerce Protocol (ACP), the
      infrastructure that lets agents transact with each other on their own. I
      wear two hats. One is developer advocacy, running the hackathons, talks,
      and docs that get people building. The other is AI engineering, building
      the systems underneath like RAG pipelines, autonomous evaluator agents,
      and multi-agent workflows that run in production.
    </p>
    <p>
      Before Virtuals I was a software engineer at Veritas Technologies, where I
      shipped full-stack features and REST APIs for enterprise software. That
      mix of production engineering and developer advocacy is the whole point
      for me. What I care about most is the moment a developer goes from reading
      about a protocol to having it actually work on their machine, and most of
      what I build and write is about closing that gap.
    </p>
  </div>
  <p style="margin:24px 0 14px;">
    <a class="btn" href="/resume.pdf" download>↓ download resume</a>
  </p>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:12px; color:var(--dim);">
    <a href="https://github.com/jxx016">github ↗</a> ·
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/johnxiangrhongsoh/">linkedin ↗</a> ·
    <a href="/rss.xml">rss</a>
  </p>
</Base>
